entry.title: Senate questions controversial Trump-nominated Judge Justin Walker

media:group.media:title: Senate questions controversial Trump-nominated Judge Justin Walker
media:group.media:description:
Judge Justin Walker, who was nominated by President Trump to the U.S. Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia early last month, will appear before the Senate Judiciary Committee for what will likely be a contentious hearing over a Trump judicial nominee.
Walker, 37, currently sits in the U.S. District Court for the Western District of Kentucky and could join what is widely considered the second most powerful bench in the United States.
Walker previously clerked for Kavanaugh during the justice's time on the D.C. Circuit Court. During the contentious confirmation saga of Supreme Court Justice Brett Kavanaugh, Walker appeared on TV regularly to defend the then-nominee.

entry.title: Are we reopening states too soon? | FOX News Rundown podcast

media:group.media:title: Are we reopening states too soon? | FOX News Rundown podcast
media:group.media:description:
Fox News Rundown podcast | May 6, 2020 Get more episodes of the Fox News Rundown podcast here: https://bit.ly/37n2wbe
Subscribe to Fox News! https://bit.ly/2vBUvAS Watch more Fox News Video: http://video.foxnews.com Watch Fox News Channel Live: http://www.foxnewsgo.com/
As states begin to reopen or plan to start up their economies and move forward from COVID-19, how safe is it for people to return to normal? What precautions need to be taken at the federal, state and local levels to keep the coronavirus from spreading and make people feel safe as we wait on a vaccine? Dr. Syra Madad is the Senior Director of New York City's System Special Pathogens Program and she joins the 'Rundown' to answer all these questions and more.
Diana Berrent tested positive for COVID in early March just as the outbreak was ramping up. She has since recovered and is trying to mobilize people like herself to help fight and better understand the virus. Berrent, founder of Survivor Corps, explains her experience battling the illness and how she is urging other survivors to donate their blood in an effort to find an effective treatment.
Plus, commentary by former Clinton pollster and managing partner of the Stagwell Group, Mark Penn.
The FOX News Rundown is a news-based daily morning podcast. Each morning, Jacqui Heinrich, Dave Anthony, Lisa Brady, Jessica Rosenthal and Chris Foster take a deep dive into the major and controversial stories of the day, tapping into the massive reporting resources of FOX News to provide a full picture of the news. You'll hear a contrast of perspectives you may not hear elsewhere while going far beyond the basic headlines. Each day The FOX News Rundown features insight from top newsmakers, along with FOX News reporters and contributors, plus a daily commentary on a significant issue of the day. Check us out each morning.
